:: CluePoint_AudreyHepburn_CLEOPATRA
<<locationheader "Audrey Hepburn">>
Ms. Hepburn's offices are housed in the main offices, which are located in an imposing building just north of Arlington National Cemetery. 31 floors tall and built in a semicircle banded in white and black, it's an unmistakable landmark. Along the top of the building are giant red letters reading "Raytheon" - a very respectable bit of monumental architecture.

You leave your vehicle to see a young man in a nice suit holding a stack of visitor badges. He briefly outlines the rules of the visit, and then begins distributing his treasures.

"Mr Vice-President," he says, handing Antony a badge. "Your Majesty." You take yours and clip it on. "Ms. Hortensia. I have one for Robert? One for Bill? And I believe these are for your bodyguards, Your Majesty. Aristonous? Here you go. Lysimachus, Peithon, Leon - I'm sorry, Leonnatus, Perdiccas, Ptolemy, and - I'm sorry, Pooestas? Ah, Peusestas. I'm sorry, with a hard k? Peucestas? Ah. Peucestas. Yes, sorry. Here you go. Now that we're all sorted, please follow me."

He takes you up to the top floor and leads you to Audrey's office where a woman, presumably her EA, waves you in. Audrey stands up from behind her desk as you enter, a smile on her face. "Antony," she says, holding out her hand, "it's good to see you again."

"Yeah, great to see you too," he says, shaking her hand. "Audrey, this is my wife, Cleopatra. Cleopatra, Audrey."

"A pleasure," you say. She holds out her hand and you perform a handshake, putting on a polite smile.

"It's all mine, Your Majesty."

"Please, call me Cleopatra."

"Well! I'm honored. Thank you very much, Cleopatra. Take a seat, please," she says, gesturing to the two chairs in front of the desk. "Would either of you like something to drink?"

